This paper deals with the problem of estimating set similarity, which is a fundamental problem in many areas of computer science such as databases, machine learning, and information retrieval. The paper proposes a memory efficient sketch method for accurately estimating Jaccard similarities in streaming sets. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DB are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with the problem of estimating set similarity and proposes a method for reducing memory usage, which are both relevant to these sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant, as the paper deals with machine learning and information retrieval problems, and proposes a method for dealing with streaming data, which are all relevant to these sub-categories.
